      <biogHist id="md5-20b0fd431404b067aa829becc10cd02e">
        <p>English scholar, Administrator, 1887-1973.  R.K. Gordon joined the University staff in 1913, having graduated from Toronto and Oxford Universities.  In 1936 he was appointed head of the Department of English and from 1943-1945 he acted as Dean of the Faculty of Arts and Science.  The Royal Society of Canada elected him a fellow in 1936.  Dr. Gordon published widely in his field of English literature, his great love being Chaucer.  He retired from the University in 1950.</p>
      </biogHist>
